library(data4soils)
library(tidyverse)
set.seed(196)
Ng <- cfbp_fpjuliet$ng

Finding the mean and variance of the Ng data

mean <- Ng |> mean()
var <- Ng |> var()

mean
## [1] 2.79164
var
## [1] 10.97915

\(f_0\)

Function \(f_0\) \[ f_0(x; a,b) = \frac{1}{b-a} \] Where \(-\infty < a < x < b < \infty\) and zero otherwise

Calculation for \(E[X]_0\) \[ \int_a^bx\frac{1}{b-a}dx = \frac{a+b}{2} = E[X]_0 \] Calculation for \(Var[X]_0\)

\[ \int_a^b\left(x-E[X]_0\right)^2\frac{1}{b-a}dx = \frac{1}{12}(a-b)^2=Var[X]_0 \]

Solving the system of equations for \(a\) and \(b\)

\[ \text{Assuming }a<b,\\\text{Solve}\left[\frac{1}{12} (a-b)^2=10.9792\land \frac{a+b}{2}=2.79164,\{a,b\}\right]\\ \\\text{ } \\\text{ }\\ a\to -2.94748,b\to 8.53076 \]

#Mathematica
Assuming[a < b, 
 Solve[1/12 (a - b)^2 == 10.9792 && (a + b)/2 == 2.79164, {a, b}]]

Fitted model \(f_0\)

\[ f_0(x) = \frac{1}{(8.531)-(-2.947)} \] and zero otherwise

or

\[ f_0(x) = 0.087 \]

ggplot() +
  theme_test() +
  geom_histogram(aes(Ng, y = ..density..),bins = 8) +
  stat_function(color = "red", size = 1,
    fun = function(x, a = -2.94748, b = 8.53076)
    (1/(b - a))
    )

\(f_1\)

Function \(f_1\)

\[ f_1(x; \mu,\sigma) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi \sigma^2}}e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{x-\mu}{\sigma}\right)^2} \]

with \(\mu > 0, -\infty < x < \infty\)

Calculation for \(E[X]_1\)

\[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}x\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi \sigma^2}}e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{x-\mu}{\sigma}\right)^2}dx=\mu=E[X]_1 \]

Calculation for \(Var[X]_1\)

\[ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty}(x-E[X]_1)^2\frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi \sigma^2}}e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{x-\mu}{\sigma}\right)^2}dx=\sigma^2=Var[X]_1 \]

Solving for \(\mu\), and \(\sigma\)

Ng |> sd()
## [1] 3.31348

\[ \mu = 2.79164\\ \sigma = 3.31348\\ \sigma^2 = 10.97915 \]

Fitted model \(f_1\) \[ f_1(x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi (3.313)^2}}e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{x-(2.792)}{3.313}\right)^2} \] Where \(-\infty < x < \infty\)

or

\[ f_1(x) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi (10.979)}}e^{-\frac{1}{2}\left(\frac{x-2.792}{3.313}\right)^2} \] Where \(-\infty < x < \infty\)

ggplot() +
  theme_test() +
  geom_histogram(aes(Ng, y = ..density..),bins = 8) +
  stat_function(color = "red", size = 1,
    fun = function(x, sigma = 3.313, mu = 2.792)
    ((1/sqrt(2*pi*sigma^2))*exp(-.5*((x - mu)/sigma)^2))
    )

\(f_2\)

Function \(f_2\)

\[ f_2(x; \alpha,\beta) = \frac{\beta^{\alpha}}{\Gamma(\alpha)}x^{\alpha-1}e^{-\beta x} \]

with \(\alpha > 0, \beta > 0, x \geq 0\) and zero otherwise

Calculation for \(E[X]_2\)

\[ \int_0^{\infty}x\frac{\beta^{\alpha}}{\Gamma(\alpha)}x^{\alpha-1}e^{-\beta x}dx=\frac{\alpha}{\beta}=E[X]_2 \]

Calculation for \(Var[X]_2\)

\[ \int_0^{\infty}(x-E[X]_2)^2\frac{\beta^{\alpha}}{\Gamma(\alpha)}x^{\alpha-1}e^{-\beta x}dx=\frac{\alpha}{\beta^2}=Var[X]_2 \]

Solving for \(\alpha\), and \(\beta\)

\[ \text{Assuming}\left[\alpha >0\land \beta >0\right]\\\text{Solve}\left[\frac{\alpha }{\beta }=2.79164\land \frac{\alpha }{\beta ^2}=10.9792,\{\alpha ,\beta \}\right]\\ \\\text{ } \\\text{ }\\ \alpha \to 0.709823,\beta \to 0.254267 \]

#Mathematica
Assuming[\[Alpha] > 0 && \[Beta] > 0, 
 Solve[\[Alpha]/\[Beta] == 2.79164 && \[Alpha]/\[Beta]^2 == 
    10.9792, {\[Alpha], \[Beta]}]]

Fitted model \(f_2\)

\[ f_2(x) = \frac{0.254^{0.710}}{\Gamma(0.710)}x^{0.710-1}e^{-0.254 x} \] Where \(x \geq 0\)

ggplot() +
  theme_test() +
  geom_histogram(aes(Ng, y = ..density..),bins = 8) +
  stat_function(color = "red", size = 1,
    fun = function(x, alpha = 0.71, beta = 0.254)
    (((beta^alpha)/gamma(alpha))*(x^(alpha - 1)*exp(-beta * x)))
    )

\(f_3\)

Function \(f_3\)

\[ f_3(x; \lambda) = \lambda e^{-\lambda x} \]

with \(\lambda > 0, x \geq 0\) and zero otherwise

Calculation for \(E[X]_3\)

\[ \int_0^{\infty}x\lambda e^{-\lambda x}dx=\frac{1}{\lambda}=E[X]_3 \]

Calculation for \(Var[X]_3\)

\[ \int_0^{\infty}(x-E[X]_3)^2\lambda e^{-\lambda x}dx=\frac{1}{\lambda^2}=Var[X]_3 \]

Solving for \(\lambda\)

\[ \text{Assuming }\lambda >0\\\text{Solve}\left[\frac{1}{\lambda }=2.79164\right] \\ \lambda \to 0.358 \]

#Mathematica
Assuming[\[Lambda] > 0, Solve[1/\[Lambda] == 2.79164]]

Fitted model \(f_3\)

\[ f_3(x; \lambda) = 0.358 e^{-0.358 x} \]

ggplot() +
  theme_test() +
  geom_histogram(aes(Ng, y = ..density..),bins = 8) +
  stat_function(color = "red", size = 1,
    fun = function(x, lambda = 0.358)
    lambda*exp(-lambda*x)
    )
